{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016zjAVNjQF4VPt4QhruNLkS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the fault. The precondition injects a fault by:\n1. Creating a fresh cluster with seed_hosts pointing to `es-cluster-*.es-cluster.default.svc.cluster.local` (wrong namespace - using `default` instead of `elasticsearch`)\n2. Scaling down to 2 replicas, deleting PVC for node-2, then scaling back to 3 replicas\n3. Waiting until there are only 2 nodes visible\n\nSo the fault is:\n1. A misconfigured `discovery.seed_hosts` pointing to the wrong namespace (`default` instead of `elasticsearch`)\n2. Node-2 can't rejoin the cluster because it can't discover the other nodes through the incorrect DNS names\n\nBut wait, I need to check the actual setup more carefully. The StatefulSet is named `es-nodes` with cluster name `es-cluster`, and the ConfigMap is `es-config`. The precondition updates the ConfigMap with seed_hosts using the wrong namespace, but the actual headless service is in the `elasticsearch` namespace, so the DNS resolution fails when node-2 tries to rejoin.\n\nLooking at the environment parameters, `BENCH_PARAM_CLUSTER_PREFIX` is set to `es-cluster`, which means the precondition should be applying resources from the seed-hosts-repair case directory using that prefix. But I'm seeing `es-nodes` as the StatefulSet name instead, so I need to check what resources are actually being deployed for this scenario.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2623,"cache_read_input_tokens":37709,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2623},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a9894363-34c2-4ba1-a8f4-f8ca4b3b113b","uuid":"7f5b11c9-8b92-4adb-