{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X8ZdN6gQB9QGBefsLXL41B","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# adversaries/elasticsearch/http-service-selector-drift\n2\t#\n3\t# The es-http Service selector is patched to use an app label that does not match any\n4\t# running Elasticsearch pod (e.g., app=es-cluster-wrong). This simulates a GitOps drift\n5\t# or an accidental kubectl patch that makes the HTTP service point at no pods, causing all\n6\t# client requests (curl, auth-checker, log-reader) to time out even though the StatefulSet\n7\t# pods are healthy. The agent must detect the broken selector, restore the correct one\n8\t# (app=es-cluster), and confirm HTTP access is working again.\n9\t\n10\tparams:\n11\t  namespace:\n12\t    default: elasticsearch\n13\t    description: Namespace the Elasticsearch Service and pods reside in.\n14\t  http_service_name:\n15\t    default: es-http\n16\t    description: Name of the Elasticsearch HTTP Service to patch.\n17\t  correct_label_value:\n18\t    default: es-cluster\n19\t    description: Correct app label value the Service selector should use.\n20\t  wrong_label_value:\n21\t    default: es-cluster-wrong\n22\t    description: Wrong app label value injected as the Service selector.\n23\t\n24\tdeploy:\n25\t  on_probe_fail: error\n26\t  probe:\n27\t    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get service {{params.http_service_name}}\"\n28\t      timeout_sec: 10\n29\t  apply:\n30\t    - command: >-\n31\t        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} patch service {{params.http_service_name}}\n32\t        --type=merge\n33\t        -p '{\"spec\":{\"selector\":{\"app\":\"{{params.wrong_label_value}}\"}}}'\n34\t      timeout_sec: 20\n35\t  verify:\n36\t    - command: >-\n37\t        /bin/sh -c \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get service {{params.http_service_name}}\n38\t        -o jsonpath='{.spec.selector.app}' | grep -q '{{params.wrong_label_value}}'\"\n39\t      timeout_sec: 15\n40\t\n41\tlift:\n42\t  on_probe_fail: skip\n43\t  probe:\n44\t    - command: >-\n45\t        /bin/sh -c \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get service {{params.http_service_name}}\n46\t        -o jsonpath='{.spec.selector.app}' | grep -q '{{params.wrong_label_value}}'\"\n47\t      timeout_sec: 15\n48\t  apply:\n49\t    - command: >-\n50\t        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} patch service {{params.http_service_name}}\n51\t        --type=merge\n52\t        -p '{\"spec\":{\"selector\":{\"app\":\"{{params.correct_label_value}}\"}}}'\n53\t      timeout_sec: 20\n54\t  verify:\n55\t    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get service {{params.http_service_name}}\"\n56\t      timeout_sec: 10\n57\t\n58\tprompt_hints:\n59\t  deploy: |\n60\t    Note: an external process may have modified Service selectors in the elasticsearch namespace.\n61\t    Verify the es-http Service selector matches the running pod labels before assuming HTTP is reachable.\n62\t  active: |\n63\t    Reminder: the es-http Service selector may be pointing at the wrong app label.\n64\t    Re-check selector vs pod labels if HTTP requests are timing out despite healthy pods.\n65\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a9894363-34c2-4ba1-a8f4-f8ca4b3b113b","uuid":"61657253-77fd-4c2a-aa8a-b38addfb6123","timestamp":"2026-06-17T09:19:42.150Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/adversaries/elasticsearch/http-service-selector-drift/scenario.yaml","content":"# adversaries/elasticsearch/http-service-selector-drift\n#\n# The es-http Service selector is patched to use an app label that does not match any\n# running Elasticsearch pod (e.g., app=es-cluster-wrong). This simulates a GitOps drift\n# or an accidental kubectl patch that makes the HTTP service point at no pods, causing all\n# client requests (curl, auth-checker, log-reader) to time out even though the StatefulSet\n# pods are healthy. The agent must detect the broken selector, restore the correct one\n# (app=es-cluster), and confirm HTTP access is working again.\n\nparams:\n  namespace:\n    default: elasticsearch\n    description: Namespace the Elasticsearch Service and pods reside in.\n  http_service_name:\n    default: es-http\n    description: Name of the Elasticsearch HTTP Service to patch.\n  correct_label_value:\n    default: es-cluster\n    description: Correct app label value the Service selector should use.\n  wrong_label_value:\n    default: es-cluster-wrong\n    description: Wrong app label value injected as the Service selector.\n\ndeploy:\n  on_probe_fail: error\n  probe:\n    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get service {{params.http_service_name}}\"\n      timeout_sec: 10\n  apply:\n    - command: >-\n        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} patch service {{params.http_service_name}}\n        --type=merge\n        -p '{\"spec\":{\"selector\":{\"app\":\"{{params.wrong_label_value}}\"}}}'\n      timeout_sec: 20\n  verify:\n    - command: >-\n        /bin/sh -c \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get service {{params.http_service_name}}\n        -o jsonpath='{.spec.selector.app}' | grep -q '{{params.wrong_label_value}}'\"\n      timeout_sec: 15\n\nlift:\n  on_probe_fail: skip\n  probe:\n    - command: >-\n        /bin/sh -c \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get service {{params.http_service_name}}\n        -o jsonpath='{.spec.selector.app}' | grep -q '{{params.wrong_label_value}}'\"\n      timeout_sec: 15\n  apply:\n    - command: >-\n        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} patch service {{params.http_service_name}}\n        --type=merge\n        -p '{\"spec\":{\"selector\":{\"app\":\"{{params.correct_label_value}}\"}}}'\n      timeout_sec: 20\n  verify:\n    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get service {{params.http_service_name}}\"\n      timeout_sec: 10\n\nprompt_hints:\n  deploy: |\n    Note: an external process may have modified Service selectors in the elasticsearch namespace.\n    Verify the es-http Service selector matches the running pod labels before assuming HTTP is reachable.\n  active: |\n    Reminder: the es-http Service selector may be pointing at the wrong app label.\n    Re-check selector vs pod labels if HTTP requests are timing out despite healthy pods.\n","numLines":65,"startLine":1,"totalLines":65}}}
